'''鼠肉'''是从[[鼠|鼠]]身上获取的[[肉类食物|肉类食物]]：用作食用的鼠類，一般採取中等體型、尾巴長的多個[[啮齿目|啮齿目]]物種。鼠肉在某些文化（例如[[西非|西非]]的[[多哥|多哥]]）屬於[[主食|主食]]{{r|newvision}}，但在另外一些文化屬於[[飲食禁忌|禁忌的]][[食物|食物]]（例如：[[東非|東非]]的[[给格族|给格族]]不會吃比山羊小的動物）<ref name="newvision">{{cite web |first=Elvina |last=Nawaguna |newspaper=Newvision Archive　|url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/D/9/38/422540 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120922012421/http://www.newvision.co.ug/D/9/38/422540 |title=Rats for dinner, a delicacy to some, a taboo to many |publisher=Newvision.co.ug |date=2005-03-10 |archive-date=2012-09-22 |access-date=2012-09-24 |language=en }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=zEtPAAAAIBAJ&sjid=CY8DAAAAIBAJ&pg=3541,6036159&dq=rat+meat+taboo&hl=en |title=Rat meat taboo |publisher=News.google.com |year=1981 |access-date=2019-05-06 |language=en |archive-date=2020-08-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809111357/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=zEtPAAAAIBAJ&sjid=CY8DAAAAIBAJ&pg=3541%2C6036159&dq=rat+meat+taboo&hl=en |dead-url=no }}</ref>，因為會帶來對疾病或饑荒的聯想。其他對鼠肉的[[禁忌|禁忌]]包括還包括對[[鼠隻|鼠隻]]所帶來的疾病或恐懼，以至在宗教上的禁止；但在許多地方（例如：[[越南|越南]]、[[馬拉維|馬拉維]]{{r|Sylvia}}），大量鼠隻為患，導致他們要把鼠肉納入地方飲食。

有些文化會有限度接納鼠肉對特定社會階層或經濟階層為可接受食物的一種：而鼠肉亦是戰亂時期生存的必要食品，因為是重要的蛋白質來源<ref name=wenweipo />。至於世界其他地方，鼠肉被認為是不潔及會帶來傳染病，所以不為社會所認可。有些宗教亦明文禁止食用鼠肉。[[伊斯蘭教法|伊斯兰教法]][[符合教規的食物_(伊斯蘭教)|禁止食用鼠肉]]。

== 地域差異 ==
=== 非洲 ===
在[[非洲|非洲]]東部的[[馬拉維|馬拉維]]，當地人會到玉米田去找尋鼠隻，並將牠們串在一起，或煮、或鹽腌、或弄乾，然後在當地的市場或街上擺賣，是當地的一種美食{{r|Sylvia}}<ref name="DailyMail">{{cite news |url=https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1205259/Making-meal-mice-Malawi.html |title=Making a meal out of mice in Malawi |newspaper=[[每日郵報|Daily Mail]]|date=2009-08-09 |access-date=2021-08-14 |language=en }}</ref><ref name="nbc">{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/id/wbna32346345 |title=Mice, anyone? They make tasty meal in Malawi |publisher=[[全國廣播公司|NBC]] |date=2009-08-10 |access-date=2021-08-14 |language=en }}</ref>。在[[撒哈拉以南非洲|撒哈拉以南非洲]]，[[蔗鼠|蔗鼠]]分佈地區的人有捕食蔗鼠的習慣<ref name="bbc">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/future/article/20151207-the-countries-where-rats-are-on-the-menu |first=Karl |last=Gruber |publisher=[[BBC|BBC]] |title=While rats are met with revulsion in most parts of the world, some communities put rodents pride of place on the dinner menu |date=2015-12-07 |access-date=2021-08-14 }}</ref>。

=== 北美洲 ===
[[燉鼠肉|燉鼠肉]]（{{lang|en|Rat stew}}）是美國[[西維珍尼亞州|西維珍尼亞州]]的一種地方飲食，源於當地過往的採礦工業；而這種習慣又可以追遡到將鼠隻[[燉煮|燉]]來吃的[[法國|法國]][[波爾多|波爾多]]吃鼠肉習慣<ref>{{cite news |last=Worrall |first=Simon |url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2015/12/151220-american-food-cuisine-local-state-ngbooktalk/ |script-title=en:What's Best, Worst, and Most Weird About American Food |website=[[National_Geographic|National Geographic]] |date=2015-12-20 |access-date=2016-01-10 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160105145241/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2015/12/151220-american-food-cuisine-local-state-ngbooktalk/ |archive-date=2016-01-05 |quote=Rat stew was born out of lean times as a result of the collapse of the mining industry}}</ref>。這道菜可算是[[路殺美食|路殺美食]]的一種<ref>{{cite book |title=廚藝好好玩：探究真正飲食科學‧破解廚房祕技‧料理好食物 |edition=全新增訂版 |url={{google books |id=g0AnDwAAQBAJ |pg=PA27 |dq=%E8%B7%AF%E6%AE%BA%E7%BE%8E%E9%A3%9F |plain-url=yes }} |authorlink=傑夫‧波特 |first=Jeff |last=Potter |year=2017 |page=25-27 |language=zh-hant }}</ref>，曾在{{tsl|en|Marlinton, West Virginia|馬靈頓}}的「路殺烹飪大賽」中出現<ref>{{cite journal |last=Pollack |first=Hilary |url=http://munchies.vice.com/articles/americas-most-beloved-regional-dishes-have-dark-and-fascinating-histories |title=America's Most Beloved Regional Dishes Have Dark and Fascinating Histories | MUNCHIES |journal=''[[Vice_(雜誌)|Vice]]'' |date=2016-01-02 |access-date=2016-01-10 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160110095110/http://munchies.vice.com/articles/americas-most-beloved-regional-dishes-have-dark-and-fascinating-histories |archive-date=2016-01-10 |quote=There were other [people] who actually celebrated the eating of rat as a culinary cultural inheritance, to the point where in Marlinton, West Virginia, for instance, they hold this annual roadkill cookoff in order to celebrate the eating of roadkill in West Virginia. When I visited the annual roadkill cookoff in Marlington, there were two folks preparing rat dishes.}}</ref>。

有些人會把[[田鼠|田鼠]]整隻連骨連內臟一起用刀柄拍碎，再丟進炭火內燒烤<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tansuocn.com/play/1361-16.html#TopPlayer |title=末日求生祕技 第二季 第4集: 混乱时代 |language=en |access-date=2014-07-02 |channel=Ch.34 Li Channel |deadurl=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411131541/http://www.tansuocn.com/play/1361-16.html#TopPlayer |archivedate=2016-04-11 }}</ref>，又會用[[松鼠|松鼠肉]]來弄餃子<ref>{{cite news |url=http://m.mingpao.com/ins/instantnews/web_tc/article/20160923/s00005/1474604077690 |title=塞松鼠屍入書包嚇死媽媽　美國8歲仔：今晚想食松鼠肉餃子 |date=2016-09-23 |publisher=[[明報|明報]] |language=zh-hant |accessdate=2016-11-11 |archive-date=2018-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180924145104/https://m.mingpao.com/ins/instantnews/web_tc/article/20160923/s00005/1474604077690 |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[西式餡餅|餡餅]]<ref name="pie">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/ukchina/trad/vert-tra-39669320 |title=從天而降 改變了英語的英國餡餅 |author=諾曼·米勒 (Norman Miller) |publisher=[[BBC|BBC]]中文 |date=2017-04-21 |access-date=2018-09-24 |language=zh |archive-date=2020-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929212325/https://www.bbc.com/ukchina/trad/vert-tra-39669320 |dead-url=no }}</ref>或[[肉餅|肉餅]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.twincities.com/2016/10/17/how-to-make-squirrel-burger-yes-ground-squirrel-meat-yum/ |title=How to make squirrel burger. Yes: Ground. Squirrel. Meat. Yum. |newspaper=TwinCities Pioneer Press |date=2016-10-17 |access-date=2019-04-26 |language=en |archive-date=2020-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125003144/https://www.twincities.com/2016/10/17/how-to-make-squirrel-burger-yes-ground-squirrel-meat-yum/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。市面上亦有售賣打獵肉食的商店有松鼠肉售賣<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wildmeat.co.uk/products/squirrel |title=Buy Squirrel Meat Online |work=Wild Meat Company |access-date=2019-05-03 |language=en |archive-date=2021-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501084618/https://www.wildmeat.co.uk/products/squirrel |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但嚴格來說，田鼠（[[倉鼠科|倉鼠科]]）和松鼠（[[松鼠科|松鼠科]]）的肉不算鼠（[[鼠科|鼠科]]）肉。

=== 亞洲 ===
[[File:Rat_meat_sold.jpg|thumb]]
[[File:Rodent_meat_dish.jpg|thumb]]的一碟炒鼠肉（很可能是[[东方田鼠|东方田鼠]]，[[倉鼠科|倉鼠科]]）]]
鼠肉一般以比較清潔的田鼠肉為主。各地食用田鼠的方法不同。例如華南地區會把田鼠腊來吃。在某些文化，鼠肉在特定的社會或經濟階層人士的限定可接受食材。在中國及[[印度|印度]]邊境生活的[[僜人|{{僻字]]，鼠肉是必須要的傳統食材，因為他們的婦女除了魚肉、豬肉、野鳥肉或鼠肉以外，其他肉類都不可以吃<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Mills | first1 = J. P. | year = 1952 | title = The Mishmis of the Lohit Valley, Assam | journal = The Journal of the Royal Anthropological Institute of Great Britain and Ireland | volume = 82 | issue = 1| pages = 1–12 | doi=10.2307/2844036| jstor = 2844036 }}</ref>。相反的，在北印度的[[穆薩哈爾|穆薩哈爾]]社區把{{tsl|en|rat farming|鼠類養殖}}商業化，因為當地人視鼠肉為極限美食<ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Heads_and_Tales/Rat_meat_to_be_commercialised_in_Bihar/articleshow/3351440.cms |dead-url=yes |title=Musahar Hindus commercialise rat farming |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090221223502/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Heads_and_Tales/Rat_meat_to_be_commercialised_in_Bihar/articleshow/3351440.cms |archive-date=2009-02-21 |language=en }}</ref>。

{{tsl|en|Ricefield rat|銀腹鼠}}（''{{tsl|en|Ricefield rat|Rattus argentiventer}}''）是一種常見於[[東南亞|東南亞]]地區的[[鼠屬|鼠屬]]物種，其肉食見於[[越南飲食|越南]]<ref name="abc">{{cite news |url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/story?id=81341 |title=Rats Back on the Menu in Vietnam |website=Abcnews.go.com |date=2006-01-06 |access-date=2016-01-10 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224052742/https://abcnews.go.com/International/story?id=81341 |archive-date=2015-12-24 |language=en }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mercurynews.com/ci_22502204/vietnamese-eat-rats-and-are-aggressive-stanford-professor |title=Vietnamese eat rats and are aggressive, Stanford professor says in article, triggering online uproar |website=Mercurynews.com |date= February 2013|access-date=2016-01-10 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224000111/http://www.mercurynews.com/ci_22502204/vietnamese-eat-rats-and-are-aggressive-stanford-professor |archive-date=2015-12-24 |language=en }}</ref><ref name="PhnomPenh">{{cite web |author=Sou Vuthy |url=http://www.phnompenhpost.com/lifestyle/rat-meat-menu-vietnam-border |title=Rat meat on the menu at the Vietnam border, Lifestyle, Phnom Penh Post |website=Phnompenhpost.com |date=2012-09-12 |access-date=2016-01-10 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224103941/http://www.phnompenhpost.com/lifestyle/rat-meat-menu-vietnam-border |archive-date=2015-12-24 |language=en }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.travelchannel.com/video/would-you-ever-eat-a-rat-12048 |title=Would You Ever Eat a Rat? VIDEO : Dining with Death |website=TravelChannel.com |access-date=2016-01-10 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140817112606/http://www.travelchannel.com/video/would-you-ever-eat-a-rat-12048 |archive-date=2014-08-17 }}</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=2019年3月}}、[[臺灣料理|臺灣]]<ref name="reuters">{{cite news |last=Jennings |first=Ralph |editor-last=Macfie |editor-first=Nick |date=2008-01-28 |title=No ratatouille on Taiwan menu, but plenty of rat |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-taiwan-rat-idUSPEK7973520080128 |newspaper=[[路透通讯社|Reuters]] |location=[[嘉義|CHIAYI]], [[台灣|Taiwan]] |access-date=2016-09-03 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110209005001/http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/28/us-taiwan-rat-idUSPEK7973520080128 |archive-date=2011-02-09 |language=en }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Huang |first=Annie |date=2002-02-10 |title=Eat, Drink, Man, Rodent |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1980&dat=20020210&id=WlEwAAAAIBAJ&pg=1119,1152405&hl=en |newspaper=The Item |volume=107 |number=118 |location=[[嘉義|CHIAYU]], [[台灣|Taiwan]] |page=10A |access-date=2016-09-03 |language=en }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/details/sketchesfromtaiw00camprich/page/131|title=Sketches from Formosa |author=William Campbell|author-link=甘為霖_(牧師)|date=1915|page=131|quote=XXII BREAKFASTING ON RATS |language=en }}</ref>、[[菲律賓飲食|菲律賓]]（然後傳往歐洲的[[西班牙飲食|西班牙]]？）及[[柬埔寨飲食|柬埔寨]]{{r|PhnomPenh}}的飲食。{{tsl|en|Rat-on-a-stick|鼠肉串}}是一種在越南、柬埔寨和泰國的人會食用的烤鼠肉料理<ref name="Molloy Duschinsky Jensen Shalka 2017">{{cite book | last1=Molloy | first1=M.J. | last2=Duschinsky | first2=P. | last3=Jensen | first3=K.F. | last4=Shalka | first4=R.J. | title=Running on Empty: Canada and the Indochinese Refugees, 1975-1980 | publisher=MQUP | series=McGill-Queen's Studies in Ethnic History | year=2017 | isbn=978-0-7735-5063-6 | url={{google books |id=ngJbDgAAQBAJ |pg=PA323 |plain-url=yes }} | page=323 | access-date=2017-07-07 | language=en }}</ref>。
除了直接燒烤，還會用醬汁來煮或煮成湯<ref name=wenweipo>{{cite news |url=http://info.wenweipo.com/index.php?action-viewnews-itemid-56448 |title=揭秘越南人為何愛吃老鼠肉 |publisher=[[文汇报_(香港)|文匯報]] |author=優樂美 |access-date=2015-07-26 |date=2012-07-29 |language=zh |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411131640/http://info.wenweipo.com/index.php?action-viewnews-itemid-56448 |archive-date=2016-04-11 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。2019年3月14日，越南的鼠肉飲食成為了《[[国家地理_(杂志)|国家地理]]》雜誌的特色內容<ref name="natgeo">{{cite news |url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/animals/2019/03/vietnam-rats-eating-food-cuisine/ |title=In Vietnam, rats are a popular food—here’s why |date=2019-03 |access-date=2019-05-02 |language=en |archive-date=2021-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121134605/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/animals/2019/03/vietnam-rats-eating-food-cuisine/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在台湾，當地過往甘蔗田遍布，故田鼠多又肥又甜，當地人叫牠們的肉作'''山河肉'''，常见与收蔗田农民带猎狗追捕田鼠大如小狗，早在1626年西班牙從馬尼拉揮軍至[[基隆市|雞籠]]灣內的[[和平島|聖薩爾瓦多島]]建立據點時，就因為補給問題而令島上幸存的駐軍以狗肉和鼠肉來充飢（參看[[臺灣西班牙統治時期#經濟|臺灣西班牙統治時期]]條目）<ref>{{cite book |title=《福爾摩沙如何變成臺灣府》|author=[[欧阳泰_(汉学家)|歐陽泰]] |pages=170-171 |publisher=[[遠流|遠流]] |date=2007-02-10 |language=zh-hant }}</ref>。

由於鼠隻的個體較小，這些肉的份量一般比較少。若要較大件的份量，需要從多隻鼠隻取出的肉塊合在一起。在越南的南部省份[[薄寮省|薄寮省]]每天上市的鼠肉至少有3噸：不同等級的鼠肉價格相差很大，鼠肉中的「極品」每公斤售兩美元，比兩公升的枝裝汽水略貴一點；但最低等的鼠肉每公斤的價錢跟兩罐汽水相若<ref name=wenweipo />，相差三到四倍。

=== 歐洲 ===
[[法国|法国]]及[[维多利亚时代|维多利亚时代]][[英国|英国]]，富人階層會吃以鼠肉製成的[[西式餡餅|西式餡餅]]。
在{{tsl|en|Rationing in the United Kingdom|英國的食物配给|第二次世界大战导致的食物配给}}期间，英国的生物学家曾經以[[实验大鼠|实验大鼠]]為食，並以[[鮮奶油|奶油]]調味<ref name="Diamond2006">{{cite book|author=Jared M. Diamond|title=Collapse: How Societies Choose to Fail Or Succeed|url=https://archive.org/details/collapse00jare|url-access=registration|quote=creamed rat.|date=January 2006|publisher=Penguin|isbn=978-0-14-303655-5|pages=[https://archive.org/details/collapse00jare/page/105 105]–}}</ref>。

一份[[波尔多|波尔多式]]的烤鼠食谱要求使用住在酒窖里的「酒鬼老鼠」。这些老鼠被剥皮和去内脏，刷上以橄榄油和碎香葱煮成的浓汁，然后在以破酒桶為燃料的火上烧烤<ref name="Schwabe1979">{{cite book|author=Calvin W. Schwabe|title=Unmentionable Cuisine|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SiBntk9jGmoC&pg=PA204|year=1979|publisher=University of Virginia Press|isbn=978-0-8139-1162-5|pages=204–|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911185523/https://books.google.com/books?id=SiBntk9jGmoC&pg=PA204#v=onepage&q&f=false|archive-date=2016-09-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bertc.com/subfive/recipes/cookingrats.htm|title=Cooking Rats and Mice|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160620090507/http://bertc.com/subfive/recipes/cookingrats.htm|archive-date=2016-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bertc.com/cooking_rats.htm|title=Cooking Rats and Mice|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160528100737/http://bertc.com/cooking_rats.htm|archive-date=2016-05-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zetatalk3.com/docs/Food/Recipes/Bertc_Weird_And_Different_Recipes_2004.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-06-23 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808175204/http://www.zetatalk3.com/docs/Food/Recipes/Bertc_Weird_And_Different_Recipes_2004.pdf |archive-date=2016-08-08 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodwine.com/food/sleuth/2000/1000/#axzz4CMByA3UP|title=Grilled Rats and Other Weird Halloween Recipes|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160722205821/http://www.foodwine.com/food/sleuth/2000/1000/#axzz4CMByA3UP|archive-date=2016-07-22}}</ref>。

在[[西班牙|西班牙]]的[[巴倫西亞省|巴倫西亞省]]，銀腹鼠的肉被[[维森特·布拉斯科·伊巴涅斯|维森特·布拉斯科·伊巴涅斯]]在他的小说《Cañas y barro》中不朽地描述。与[[鰻|鳗鱼]]和被称为''garrafons''的当地豆子一起，{{tsl|en|Southwestern water vole|西南部水䶄}}（''{{tsl|en|Southwestern water vole|Arvicola sapidus}}''，亦作「[[沼泽鼠|沼泽鼠]]」）是[[西班牙大鍋飯|西班牙大鍋飯]]的主要成分之一，後現時普遍已被兔肉、鸡肉和海鲜所取代<ref>Manuel Vázquez Montalbán, ''La cocina de los mediterráneos'', Ediciones B – Mexico</ref>。



===中、南太平洋===
In the traditional cultures of the <!-- [[Hawaiians|Hawaiians]] -->[[夏威夷族|夏威夷族]] and the <!-- [[Polynesians|Polynesians]] -->[[波利尼西亚人|波利尼西亚人]], rat was an everyday food for commoners. When feasting, the Polynesian people of <!-- [[Rapa_Nui|Rapa Nui]] -->[[復活節島|復活節島]] could eat rat meat, but the king was not allowed to, due to the islanders' belief in his "state of sacredness" called {{tsl|en|Tapu (Polynesian culture)||''tapu''}}.<ref>Leach, Helen. (February 2003) ''Did East Polynesians Have a Concept of Luxury Foods?'' World Archaeology, Vol. 34, No. 3, Luxury Foods. pp. 442–457.</ref> In studying precontact archaeological sites in <!-- [[Hawaii|Hawaii]] -->[[夏威夷州|夏威夷州]], archaeologists have found the concentration of the remains of rats associated with commoner households accounted for three times the animal remains associated with elite households. The rat bones found in all sites are fragmented, burned and covered in carbonized material, indicating the rats were eaten as food. The greater occurrence of rat remains associated with commoner households may indicate the elites of precontact Hawaii did not consume them as a matter of status or taste.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Kirch | first1 = Patrick V. | last2 = Sharyn Jones | first2 = O'Day | year = 2003 | title = New Archaeological Insights into Food and Status: A Case Study from Pre-Contact Hawaii. | journal = World Archaeology | volume = 34 | issue = 3| pages = 484–497 | doi=10.1080/0043824021000026468| s2cid = 161955651 }}</ref>

===其他地區===
在無界其他地區，鼠肉往往被認為是帶病及不潔，不為社會接受，又或因為強烈的宗教禁令而被拒抗。根據[[伊斯兰教|伊斯蘭教]]的《[[符合教規的食物_(伊斯蘭教)|符合教規的食物]]》和[[犹太教|犹太教]]的《[[犹太教饮食规定|饮食规定]]》傳統上禁止鼠肉的食用，而在[[南美洲|南美洲]][[秘魯|秘魯]]的{{tsl|en|Shipibo people|Shipibo人}}和[[玻利維亞|玻利維亞]]的{{tsl|en|Sirionó people|Sirionó人}}認為食用鼠隻昰種文化上的禁忌<ref>{{cite journal |last=Behrens |first=Clifford A. |date=1986-09 |title=''Shipibo Food Categorization and Preference: Relationships between Indigenous and Western Dietary Concepts'' |journal=''[[American_Anthropologist|American Anthropologist]]'', Nathan New Series |volume=88 |issue=3 |pages=647–658 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Priest |first=Perry N. |date=1996-10 |title=''Provision for the Aged among the Sirionó Indians of Bolivia'' |journal=''American Anthropologist'', New Series |volume=68 |issue=5 |pages=1245–1247 |language=en}}</ref>。

== 作為寵物的食物 ==
鼠類是[[蛇|蛇類]]常見的食物，不管是野生的還是作為寵物飼養的。{{tsl|en|rat snake|鼠蛇}}是[[游蛇科|游蛇科]]{{tsl|en|Colubrinae|黄颔蛇亚科}}（{{lang|la|Colubrinae}}，不是水游蛇科）多個屬物種的泛稱；牠們連同[[球蟒|球蟒]]都是一些以鼠類為主食的物種。即使被人類所飼養，牠們都會被飼主餵食新鮮或雪藏的鼠肉，不管牠們是由寵物店或動物園所飼養。在英國，[[動物福利條例2006|動物福利條例2006]]（{{lang|en|Animal Welfare Act 2006}}）立例禁止對動物餵食活生生的動物：法例規定用於餵飼的動物必須已死亡，除非這對被餵飼動物的健康有影響<ref>{{cite web |url=https://faunalytics.org/the-feeding-of-live-food-to-exotic-pets-issues-of-welfare-and-ethics/ |script-title=Live-Feeding Prey to Captive Predators |trans-title=對被圈養的捕食動物餵飼活生生的獵物 |publisher=faunalytics.org |date=2014-10-17 |access-date=2021-08-14 |language=en }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2006/45/contents |title=Animal Welfare Act 2006 |work=lesgislation.gov.uk |access-date=2021-08-14 }}</ref>。這法例是基於來自[[英國皇家防止虐待動物協會|英國皇家防止虐待動物協會]]的壓力，指給其他動物餵飼活生生的哺乳類動物過於殘忍。

== 味道及營養 ==
來自野生的鼠肉含有較低的脂肪。由於囓齒動物以稻米、水果和蔬菜為食，它們的肉含豐富的[[Ω-3脂肪酸|ω-3脂肪酸]]。鼠肉的味道隨牠們所吃的食物而有所不同。據說食用稻米的鼠肉嘗起來像[[兔肉|兔肉]]<ref name=":2" />。甘蔗鼠有一種甜白的肉，味道介於豬肉、鷓鴣肉或野兔肉之間<ref name=":2" />。據說，在19世紀，[[吉伦特河口|吉伦特河口]]的鼠隻吃得飽飽的，肉質鮮美，帶有[[麝香|麝香]]的味道，並沒有令食客不快的感覺<ref name=":5" />。

==歷史==
人類很早就以鼠肉為食物，[[唐朝|唐朝]]時期，嶺南獠民喜饗蜜唧，“即鼠胎未瞬，通身赤蠕者”，北宋[[蘇軾|蘇軾]]在嶺南及[[海南島|海南島]]也吃過鼠肉，有詩云：“朝盤見蜜唧，夜枕聞[[鵂鶹|鵂鶹]]。”蘇軾在海南島還寄詩給在惠州的弟弟子由云：“土人頓頓食薯芋，薦以熏鼠燒蝙蝠；舊聞蜜唧嘗嘔吐，稍近蝦蟆緣習俗。”

==食用安全==
雖然鼠肉「溫良大補」<ref name="apple20171216">{{cite news | url = https://hk.news.appledaily.com/china/realtime/article/20171216/57584364 | title = 【極度兇殘】街頭淥鼠活剝皮 佛山大叔：有益過雞肉 | date = 2017-12-16 | access-date = 2017-12-17 | publisher = [[蘋果日報_(香港)|蘋果日報 (香港)]] | language = zh-hant | archive-date = 2019-06-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190605034245/https://hk.news.appledaily.com/china/realtime/article/20171216/57584364 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，但對於鼠肉食用者來說，鼠肉的來源以及安全性更為重要。對於討厭老鼠的人，他們會用毒鼠藥來毒殺鼠類。食用這些受毒藥污染的鼠肉有可能致命<ref name="mingpao20160923">{{cite news |url=http://news.mingpao.com/ins/instantnews/web_tc/article/20160923/s00004/1474555905195 |title=街邊檔食3肉串後嘔吐尿血　雲南13歲男證鼠藥中毒　疑無良商販死老鼠加工製肉 |publisher=[[明報|明報]] |date=2016-09-23 |language=zh-hant |accessdate=2016-11-11 |archive-date=2017-12-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201131753/https://news.mingpao.com/ins/instantnews/web_tc/article/20160923/s00004/1474555905195 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
所以不得不小心謹慎。

根據一項於2020年進行的研究，在越南南部三個省份的野生動物貿易進行檢疫。研究發現在受調查的餐廳，有55%所發售的田鼠被驗出帶有一種[[冠状病毒|冠状病毒]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/19/science/coronavirus-rats-vietnam.html |title=Wildlife Trade Spreads Coronaviruses as Animals Get to Market |newspaper=[[紐約時報|The New York Times]] |access-date=2021-08-11 |language=en }}</ref>

